author: COMSOL
description: In static mixers, the fluid is pumped through a pipe containing stationary baffles. This mixing technique is particularly well suited for laminar flow mixing because it gives small pressure losses in this flow regime. In this example, the flow in a twisted blade static mixer is studied.
label: laminar_static_mixer.mph
